---
description: Pancreator self-development workflow control rules
alwaysApply: true
---

The terms MUST, MUST NOT, SHOULD, SHOULD NOT, and MAY use RFC 2119 meanings.

You MUST read `AGENTS.md`, `runtime/target-repo-primer.md`, and `runtime/repository-checks.json` before expanding repository context. You MUST NOT follow primer references unless a concrete task-specific need requires the referenced file. You MUST use `./bin/pan` and MUST NOT hand-edit runtime state. You MUST read the active invocation card before expanding context. Operator approvals and irreversible actions MUST remain operator-owned. TypeScript changes MUST conform to `governance/handbooks/typescript/style-guide.md`.

For source-allowed systematic stages, agents MAY edit tracked files directly within declared scope and MUST NOT hand-edit the workspace index or generated run records. Pancreator does not create persistent workspace locks or leases, so concurrent mutating workflows against the same workspace are forbidden by governance rather than blocked by stale state. Per-file `pan changes begin|commit|cancel` is deprecated and retained only as a no-op compatibility surface. An operator-selected `/pan-spotfix` MAY edit tracked files directly only under `library/skills/spotfix.md` and only when no mutating workflow agent is executing against the same workspace.
